}cunning{/sc} {sc}crafty{/sc} {sc}wily{/sc} {sc}tricky{/sc} {sc}foxy{/sc} {sc}artful{/sc} {sc}slick{/sc} mean attaining or seeking to attain one's ends by guileful or devious means. {sc}sly{/sc} implies furtiveness, lack of candor, and skill in concealing one's aims and methods. "], ["vis", [{"t": "a {it}sly{/it} corporate raider"}]], ["text", " {sc}cunning{/sc} suggests the inventive use of sometimes limited intelligence in overreaching or circumventing. "], ["vis", [{"t": "the {it}cunning{/it} fox avoided the trap"}]], ["text", " {sc}crafty{/sc} implies cleverness and subtlety of method. "], ["vis", [{"t": "a {it}crafty{/it} lefthander"}]], ["text", " {sc}wily{/sc} implies skill and deception in maneuvering. "], ["vis", [{"t": "the {it}wily{/it} fugitive escaped the posse"}]], ["text", " {sc}tricky{/sc} is more likely to suggest shiftiness and unreliability than skill in deception and maneuvering. "], ["vis", [{"t": "a {it}tricky{/it} political operative"}]], ["text", " {sc}foxy{/sc} implies a shrewd and wary craftiness usually involving devious dealing. "], ["vis", [{"t": "a {it}foxy{/it} publicity man planting stories"}]], ["text", " {sc}artful{/sc} implies indirectness in dealing and often connotes sophistication or cleverness. "], ["vis", [{"t": "elicited the information by {it}artful{/it} questioning"}]], ["text", " {sc}slick{/sc} emphasizes smoothness and guile. "], ["vis", [{"t": "{it}slick{/it} operators selling time-sharing"}]]]}], "et": [["text", "Middle English {it}sleighe, sli{/it}, from Old Norse {it}sl\u0153gr{/it}; akin to Old English {it}sl\u0113an{/it} to strike {ma}{mat|slay|}{/ma}"]], "date": "13th century{ds||1|a|}", "shortdef": ["wise in practical affairs", "displaying cleverness : ingenious", "clever in concealing one's aims or ends : furtive"]}]